classifications.description: ICT specially adapted for medical diagnosis, medical simulation or medical data mining; ICT specially adapted for detecting, monitoring or modelling epidemics or pandemics for computer-aided diagnosis, e.g. based on medical expert systems
ICT specially adapted for the handling or processing of medical references relating to pathologies
Information and communication technologies [ICT] supporting adaptation to climate change, e.g. for weather forecasting or climate simulation

abstract: Access, analysis and processing medical-related data in an integrated knowledge base is initiated by one of a plurality of initiating events, such as a user query, the occurrence of a medical event, a change of state of data within the knowledge base, and a system-generated initiating event, such as based upon attaining various triggering levels or expiration of. The integrated knowledge base may be physically located in quite disparate locations, and processing strings may occur on one or more computer system. The triggering events begin specific processing based upon algorithms which can respond to the specific triggering event, or can analyze data in manners not necessarily requested by the triggering event. The technique thus permits analysis of a wide range of medical-related data for user-related purposes, patient-related purposes, as well as to identify and discover particular medical care needs or relationships between data to enhance diagnosis, treatment, institutional performance, and so forth.
claims:
1. A method for initiating a processing string for processing, performing a computer-assisted data operation on, analyzing or acquiring medical care related data, the method comprising: 
monitoring a plurality of distinct processing string initiating inputs for any one of a plurality of initiating events;  upon detection of one of the plurality of possible initiating events on the inputs, accessing data from an integrated knowledge base, the integrated knowledge base including data derived from a plurality of controllable and prescribable data resources;  processing, performing a computer-assisted data operation on, or analyzing the accessed data or initiating acquisition of additional data in accordance with one of a plurality of distinct processing strings at least to identify a relationship among accessed or acquired data from controllable and prescribable data resources of at least two different modalities; and  communicating an output to a user based upon the processing, operation, analysis or acquisition.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein the initiating events include a user query and a medical event occurrence.
3. The method of claim 1, wherein the initiating events include a change in a state of data within the integrated knowledge base.

4. The method of claim 1, wherein the initiating events include a system-generated processing string initiating event occurring independent of user queries, medical event occurrences and changes in states of data within the integrated knowledge base.
5. The method of claim 1, wherein a plurality of different processing strings are initiated in response to detection of the one of the plurality of possible initiating events on the inputs.
6. The method of claim 5, wherein the processing strings include a string adapted to identify a risk factor indicated by the data from the different resource modalities.
7. The method of claim 1, wherein at least one of the processing strings includes analysis of the data for identification of a patient diagnosis.

8. The method of claim 1, wherein at least one of the processing strings includes analysis of the data for identification of a relationship among data indicative of a theoretical medical condition identification model.
9. The method of claim 1, wherein the controllable and prescribable data resources include at least two different resource types.
10. The method of claim 9, wherein the data include patient-specific clinical data acquired at different points in time.

11. The method of claim 10, wherein the analysis is at least partially performed based upon a computer-assisted diagnosis algorithm, a computer-assisted processing algorithm or a computer-assisted acquisition algorithm acting on the accessed data.
12. The method of claim 11, wherein the processing, analysis or acquisition is performed to identify at least on trend in a patient characteristic.

13. The method of claim 12, wherein the integrated knowledge base includes data derived from data specific to a patient of interest analyzed in combination with data representative of characteristics of a plurality of physiological conditions.
14. The method of claim 1, wherein the data includes financial data, and wherein the user includes a medical care financing organization.

monitoring a plurality of distinct processing string initiating inputs for any one of a plurality of initiating events;  upon detection of one of the plurality of possible initiating events on the inputs, accessing data from an integrated knowledge base, the integrated knowledge base including data derived from a plurality of controllable and prescribable data resources of different types;  processing, performing a computer-assisted data operation on, or analyzing the accessed data or initiating acquisition of additional data in accordance with one of a plurality of distinct processing strings to identify a relationship among accessed or acquired data from controllable and prescribable data resources of at least two different types; and  communicating an output to a user based upon the processing, operation, analysis or acquisition.
